description.text: Insert a sterile swab into the nostril of the patient, swab over the surface of the posterior nasopharynx. Withdraw the sterile swab from the nasal cavity.
Insert swab into an extraction buffer tube. While squeezing the buffer tube, stir the swab more than 5 times.
Remove the swab while squeezing the sides of the tube to extract the liquid from the swab.
Collect 350uL of mixture from the collection tube and mix with the extraction buffer.
